results.name: Let x = RootOf( z^2+z+1 ) and y = 1+x. Number of 4-ary Lyndon words of length n over GF(4) with trace 1 and subtrace x.
comment: Also the number of 4-ary Lyndon words of length n over GF(4) with trace 1 and subtrace y. Also the number of 4-ary Lyndon words of length n over GF(4) with trace x and subtrace 1. Also the number of 4-ary Lyndon words of length n over GF(4) with trace x and subtrace x. Also the number of 4-ary Lyndon words of length n over GF(4) with trace y and subtrace 1. Also the number of 4-ary Lyndon words of length n over GF(4) with trace y and subtrace y.
Is this a duplicate of A074032? - _R. J. Mathar_, Dec 15 2020
link: Frank Ruskey, 4-ary Lyndon words with given trace and subtrace over GF(4)
